mbed-cli not used in this project

**mbed-os sha:**
mbed-os version 5.6.6

**Expected behavior**
The STM32 board has to emulate a USB keyboard compatible with any USB port

**Actual behavior**
The code is stuck and doesn't go further, I have some prints that are not displayed on the terminal

**Steps to reproduce**

The USBDevice library has to be fixed. The code is probably stuck at the USBDevice::connect(bool blocking) function. I use the USBDevice library made by ST available here: https://os.mbed.com/teams/ST/code/USBDEVICE/#d9c7334e2183

If I use the parenthesis on my declaration of USBKeyboard I get this error: 
       request for member 'printf' in 'key', which is of non-class type 'USBKeyboard()'
When I try to do: key.printf("Hello World\r\n");

This is the main.cpp file I use for this project:


```
#include "mbed.h"
#include "USBKeyboard.h"

DigitalOut led_green(LED3);
DigitalOut led_red(LED4);

USBKeyboard key;

InterruptIn user_button(USER_BUTTON);

bool button_state;

void button_pressed()
{
    button_state=true;
}

void button_released()
{
    button_state=false;
}

int main(){
    while(1){
        led_green=1;
        led_red=1;
        user_button.rise(&button_pressed);
        user_button.fall(&button_released);
        if(button_state) {
           printf("Writing\n");
           key.printf("Hello World\r\n");
           led_green=1;
           led_red=0;
        }
        else{
            led_green=0;
            led_red=1;
        } 
        wait(1);
    }
}

```

